WEBVTT

1
00:00:01.459 --> 00:00:03.059
On this episode of "expedition files"...

2
00:00:04.671 --> 00:00:07.716
In 1975. union leader Jimmy hoffa

3
00:00:07.841 --> 00:00:10.260
vanishes from a parking
lot without a trace.

4
00:00:12.679 --> 00:00:16.349
Was it a mob hit? If
so. where's the body?

5
00:00:16.474 --> 00:00:18.018
A new theory may finally solve

6
00:00:18.143 --> 00:00:21.062
one of the FBI's
longest-running investigations.

7
00:00:25.358 --> 00:00:29.255
Then. the holy grail.
the cup of Jesus Christ.

8
00:00:29.279 --> 00:00:31.698
has been hunted by
kings and crusaders.

9
00:00:33.074 --> 00:00:35.326
This biblical relic was said to be lost.

10
00:00:36.327 --> 00:00:37.704
Has it now been found?

11
00:00:41.583 --> 00:00:45.146
And groundbreaking engineer
Rudolf diesel disappears on

12
00:00:45.170 --> 00:00:48.190
an ocean liner while
transporting secret plans that

13
00:00:48.214 --> 00:00:51.384
could change the course of world war I.

14
00:00:51.509 --> 00:00:54.054
We reveal what may have
been one of the greatest

15
00:00:54.179 --> 00:00:56.389
espionage operations in history.

16
00:01:00.310 --> 00:01:01.728
In the corridors of time...

17
00:01:04.230 --> 00:01:06.983
Are mysteries that defy explanation.

18
00:01:08.735 --> 00:01:12.030
Now. I'm traveling through history itself...

19
00:01:14.866 --> 00:01:16.367
On a search for the truth.

20
00:01:18.912 --> 00:01:19.913
New evidence.

21
00:01:21.831 --> 00:01:22.916
Shocking answers.

22
00:01:25.085 --> 00:01:26.086
I'm Josh gates.

23
00:01:27.504 --> 00:01:28.505
And these...

24
00:01:30.590 --> 00:01:32.258
Are my expedition files.

25
00:01:36.930 --> 00:01:40.266
One of my first jobs out of
college was working as a waiter

26
00:01:40.391 --> 00:01:43.269
at a Hollywood institution
called the magic castle.

27
00:01:43.394 --> 00:01:45.438
a private club for magicians.

28
00:01:45.563 --> 00:01:47.666
I learned two things working there.

29
00:01:47.690 --> 00:01:49.877
One. magicians are lousy tippers.

30
00:01:49.901 --> 00:01:52.612
And two. there's nothing
an audience loves more than

31
00:01:52.737 --> 00:01:54.507
watching something disappear.

32
00:01:54.531 --> 00:01:56.825
So tonight. prepare to be amazed

33
00:01:56.950 --> 00:02:00.846
as we take vanishing acts to
their most shocking extreme.

34
00:02:00.870 --> 00:02:05.434
I promise. no top hats.
rabbits. or $1 tips in sight.

35
00:02:05.458 --> 00:02:07.627
We examine three of history's most

36
00:02:07.752 --> 00:02:11.464
extraordinary disappearances...
people and things that were

37
00:02:11.589 --> 00:02:13.299
suddenly gone without a trace.

38
00:02:13.424 --> 00:02:15.510
leaving the rest of the world guessing.

39
00:02:15.635 --> 00:02:17.905
That is. until now.

40
00:02:17.929 --> 00:02:21.349
We begin on July 30. 1975.

41
00:02:21.474 --> 00:02:25.746
It's a muggy afternoon
just after 2:30 P.M.

42
00:02:25.770 --> 00:02:29.125
I'm standing outside the
machus red fox restaurant.

43
00:02:29.149 --> 00:02:31.794
about 20 miles northwest of Detroit.

44
00:02:31.818 --> 00:02:32.878
The guy on the payphone here?

45
00:02:32.902 --> 00:02:35.589
He isn't just your average angry diner.

46
00:02:35.613 --> 00:02:38.592
In fact. he's one of the most
powerful men in america.

47
00:02:38.616 --> 00:02:40.469
This is Jimmy hoffa.

48
00:02:40.493 --> 00:02:43.954
At 62. hoffa is the former
president of the teamsters.

49
00:02:43.997 --> 00:02:46.875
the most formidable
labor union in america.

50
00:02:47.000 --> 00:02:49.436
Right now. he's on the
phone with his wife. Josephine.

51
00:02:49.460 --> 00:02:52.338
upset that he's been stood
up for a crucial meeting.

52
00:02:52.463 --> 00:02:54.233
He tells her to throw
some steaks on the grill

53
00:02:54.257 --> 00:02:56.819
and expect him back by 4 o'clock.

54
00:02:56.843 --> 00:02:59.345
But those steaks. well.
they're gonna go cold.

55
00:02:59.470 --> 00:03:02.616
And Jimmy hoffa isn't coming
home for dinner. because just

56
00:03:02.640 --> 00:03:04.785
minutes from now. he'll disappear.

57
00:03:04.809 --> 00:03:07.187
setting off one of the most extraordinary

58
00:03:07.312 --> 00:03:10.023
missing persons cases in history.

59
00:03:10.148 --> 00:03:12.293
For over 50 years. the world will ask

60
00:03:12.317 --> 00:03:16.338
the same question... what
really happened to Jimmy hoffa?

61
00:03:16.362 --> 00:03:19.032
And why has his body
never been found?

62
00:03:35.548 --> 00:03:37.926
In the middle of the last
century. pretty much everyone

63
00:03:38.051 --> 00:03:41.780
knows the name. Jimmy
hoffa. To millions. he's a hero.

64
00:03:41.804 --> 00:03:44.033
As teamster president.
he stands up against

65
00:03:44.057 --> 00:03:47.119
big business to secure
better wages and benefits for

66
00:03:47.143 --> 00:03:49.103
the blue-collar workers who depend on it.

67
00:03:57.070 --> 00:03:58.404
You've heard of the supply chain?

68
00:03:59.405 --> 00:04:03.135
The vast network that moves
goods from factories to stores.

69
00:04:03.159 --> 00:04:06.287
Well. in the 20th century.
the teamsters control it.

70
00:04:06.412 --> 00:04:09.123
The organization of truck
drivers and warehouse workers

71
00:04:09.249 --> 00:04:12.252
literally keeps the
American economy moving.

72
00:04:12.377 --> 00:04:13.562
Hoffa rises through the ranks

73
00:04:13.586 --> 00:04:16.256
as a street-fighting labor organizer.

74
00:04:16.381 --> 00:04:19.425
He becomes union president in 1957.

75
00:04:19.550 --> 00:04:22.428
His influence is undeniable.
but his methods are often

76
00:04:22.553 --> 00:04:24.264
controversial. even illegal.

77
00:04:28.309 --> 00:04:31.145
You see. in the '50s.
organized crime has its hooks

78
00:04:31.271 --> 00:04:33.106
in a lot of local unions.

79
00:04:33.231 --> 00:04:36.001
In return for their loyalty
and occasional muscle.

80
00:04:36.025 --> 00:04:38.987
hoffa lets mob-connected
businessmen borrow massive

81
00:04:39.112 --> 00:04:42.258
chunks of money from
the teamsters pension fund.

82
00:04:42.282 --> 00:04:45.618
That money helps build glitzy
Vegas hotels and casinos.

83
00:04:48.329 --> 00:04:51.165
The mob gets low-interest
loans. and in exchange.

84
00:04:51.291 --> 00:04:54.168
they give union jobs to
teamsters. everyone from

85
00:04:54.294 --> 00:04:55.503
bellhops to cabbies.

86
00:05:00.133 --> 00:05:02.361
Workers adore hoffa. The government?

87
00:05:02.385 --> 00:05:05.013
Not so much. especially
Attorney General

88
00:05:05.138 --> 00:05:06.573
Robert f. Kennedy.

89
00:05:06.597 --> 00:05:08.742
See. it's not just hoffa's
mob buddies who are

90
00:05:08.766 --> 00:05:09.809
breaking the law.

91
00:05:09.934 --> 00:05:12.579
Hoffa plays dirty himself... extortion.

92
00:05:12.603 --> 00:05:15.040
wiretapping. embezzlement.

93
00:05:15.064 --> 00:05:18.919
In 1967. after years of
attempts. the feds. led by

94
00:05:18.943 --> 00:05:21.863
Kennedy. finally nailed
Jimmy for jury tampering

95
00:05:21.988 --> 00:05:24.073
and misusing union pension funds.

96
00:05:25.241 --> 00:05:27.493
He gets 13 years behind bars.

97
00:05:32.623 --> 00:05:34.226
With his raincoat covering handcuffs.

98
00:05:34.250 --> 00:05:37.337
hoffa arrives at federal prison
in lewisburg. Pennsylvania.

99
00:05:40.173 --> 00:05:44.403
It seems the street-fighting labor
boss has finally met his match.

100
00:05:44.427 --> 00:05:46.447
But don't count hoffa out just yet.

101
00:05:46.471 --> 00:05:49.408
He's about to get help
from a very unlikely friend.

102
00:05:49.432 --> 00:05:51.184
president Richard Nixon.

103
00:05:51.309 --> 00:05:54.663
On December 23.
1971. Nixon commutes

104
00:05:54.687 --> 00:05:57.583
hoffa's sentence. and
Jimmy gets out after serving

105
00:05:57.607 --> 00:05:59.585
less than five years.

106
00:05:59.609 --> 00:06:02.421
Nixon thinks that freeing
him will earn him support from

107
00:06:02.445 --> 00:06:03.905
hoffa's loyal followers.

108
00:06:07.617 --> 00:06:10.137
But for hoffa. freedom
comes with a caveat.

109
00:06:10.161 --> 00:06:14.183
Nixon bars him from any
union activity until 1980.

110
00:06:14.207 --> 00:06:16.876
effectively minimizing
his power and influence.

111
00:06:18.544 --> 00:06:22.983
In 1974. hoffa sues the
government to lift the ban.

112
00:06:23.007 --> 00:06:25.885
With an appeal underway.
hoffa tries to shore up support

113
00:06:26.010 --> 00:06:27.863
for a run at the union presidency

114
00:06:27.887 --> 00:06:29.490
at the next election...

115
00:06:29.514 --> 00:06:31.992
which brings us back to
the restaurant parking lot

116
00:06:32.016 --> 00:06:35.061
on that muggy day in July of 1975.

117
00:06:36.729 --> 00:06:39.333
When hoffa fails to
arrive home. his family

118
00:06:39.357 --> 00:06:40.667
calls the police.

119
00:06:40.691 --> 00:06:43.778
The next morning.
investigators find hoffa's car

120
00:06:43.903 --> 00:06:46.280
in the machus red fox parking lot.

121
00:06:46.406 --> 00:06:50.118
There's no sign of a
struggle and no sign of Jimmy.

122
00:06:50.243 --> 00:06:52.888
Several people report seeing
the famous labor leader at

123
00:06:52.912 --> 00:06:54.848
the restaurant the day before.

124
00:06:54.872 --> 00:06:57.059
One witness claims she saw hoffa

125
00:06:57.083 --> 00:07:00.795
get into a maroon Mercury
sedan with three other men.

126
00:07:00.920 --> 00:07:04.674
It is the last time anyone
will report seeing hoffa alive.

127
00:07:08.219 --> 00:07:10.095
A nationwide manhunt is launched.

128
00:07:13.599 --> 00:07:16.310
As it heats up. rumors
circulate that the mafia

129
00:07:16.436 --> 00:07:18.271
is involved in hoffa's disappearance.

130
00:07:19.772 --> 00:07:22.775
Hoffa's family finds his date
book. and it makes the mob

131
00:07:22.900 --> 00:07:24.336
the prime suspect.

132
00:07:24.360 --> 00:07:27.613
It reveals the names of two
men he intended to meet that day

133
00:07:27.738 --> 00:07:28.739
at the restaurant.

134
00:07:30.366 --> 00:07:34.263
Tony giacalone. aka
Tony Jack. a senior figure in

135
00:07:34.287 --> 00:07:35.371
the Detroit mob.

136
00:07:36.873 --> 00:07:42.020
And Tony provenzano. aka
Tony pro. a "capo" or captain

137
00:07:42.044 --> 00:07:43.629
for the genovese crime family.

138
00:07:45.173 --> 00:07:47.675
Investigators track down both Tonys.

139
00:07:47.800 --> 00:07:50.571
Each has a strong alibi
and deny that a meeting with

140
00:07:50.595 --> 00:07:52.096
hoffa was even scheduled.

141
00:07:57.310 --> 00:08:00.188
But there is a thread for
the investigators to pull on.

142
00:08:00.313 --> 00:08:03.524
Tony giacalone's son happens
to own a Mercury sedan.

143
00:08:03.649 --> 00:08:06.462
just like the one the
eyewitness described.

144
00:08:06.486 --> 00:08:08.863
And there's another interesting wrinkle.

145
00:08:08.988 --> 00:08:12.158
A man called Chucky o'brien
borrowed the car that morning

146
00:08:12.283 --> 00:08:14.303
to supposedly run some errands.

147
00:08:14.327 --> 00:08:17.264
Chucky was a known
hoffa union associate.

148
00:08:17.288 --> 00:08:18.998
Jimmy treated him like a stepson.

149
00:08:23.419 --> 00:08:26.380
When authorities process
the car. they find bloodstains

150
00:08:26.506 --> 00:08:28.841
on the seat. and that's not all.

151
00:08:28.966 --> 00:08:31.552
A few strands of hair
matching hoffa's color

152
00:08:31.677 --> 00:08:34.388
also go into evidence bags.

153
00:08:34.514 --> 00:08:37.910
Police dogs hit on hoffa's
scent. suggesting Jimmy was in

154
00:08:37.934 --> 00:08:40.937
the back seat and. even
more disturbingly. the trunk.

155
00:08:44.023 --> 00:08:46.192
But o'brien claims he
didn't pick Jimmy up

156
00:08:46.317 --> 00:08:48.295
at the machus red fox that day.

157
00:08:48.319 --> 00:08:50.238
And the blood on the seat?

158
00:08:50.363 --> 00:08:52.865
Chucky says that comes
from a salmon he delivered to

159
00:08:52.990 --> 00:08:54.367
a teamster's house that morning.

160
00:08:57.620 --> 00:09:01.099
If this all sounds very fishy
to you. you're not alone.

161
00:09:01.123 --> 00:09:04.019
However. tests on the
blood reveal o'brien is telling

162
00:09:04.043 --> 00:09:06.379
the truth. at least about the salmon.

163
00:09:06.504 --> 00:09:08.548
It's fish blood. not human.

164
00:09:08.673 --> 00:09:11.109
As to the hair. well. it's the mid-'70s.

165
00:09:11.133 --> 00:09:14.279
and we're more than a decade
away from DNA technology that

166
00:09:14.303 --> 00:09:16.973
could confirm whether
it belonged to hoffa.

167
00:09:19.559 --> 00:09:20.827
Days turn to weeks.

168
00:09:20.851 --> 00:09:23.396
and there's still no sign of Jimmy.

169
00:09:23.521 --> 00:09:26.291
In November of 1975.
nearly four months

170
00:09:26.315 --> 00:09:29.836
after the disappearance.
investigators catch a break.

171
00:09:29.860 --> 00:09:32.947
Ralph picardo. a
mob-connected convict serving

172
00:09:33.072 --> 00:09:35.551
time for murder. claims
he knows the truth of

173
00:09:35.575 --> 00:09:39.078
hoffa's disappearance and
gives up the details to the feds in

174
00:09:39.203 --> 00:09:41.682
exchange for a reduced sentence.

175
00:09:41.706 --> 00:09:44.977
Ralph points the finger at
the two Tonys. saying they sent

176
00:09:45.001 --> 00:09:49.130
four wise guys to kidnap
hoffa from the machus red fox.

177
00:09:49.255 --> 00:09:51.424
and that they took him
to a second location

178
00:09:51.549 --> 00:09:53.217
where he was shot and killed.

179
00:10:01.684 --> 00:10:04.437
Then. according to picardo.
the body was packed into

180
00:10:04.562 --> 00:10:07.481
a 55-gallon drum. loaded on a truck.

181
00:10:07.607 --> 00:10:10.711
and driven to a mob-controlled
landfill in New Jersey.

182
00:10:10.735 --> 00:10:11.944
where it was buried.

183
00:10:15.156 --> 00:10:17.884
However. several days of
searching at the dump turns up

184
00:10:17.908 --> 00:10:21.013
little more than toxic waste
and animal bones. likely

185
00:10:21.037 --> 00:10:23.539
discarded from nearby
meat processing plants.

186
00:10:24.832 --> 00:10:29.670
In late 1975. a grand jury
grills Tony pro. Tony Jack.

187
00:10:29.795 --> 00:10:33.233
and several of the other
alleged mob co-conspirators.

188
00:10:33.257 --> 00:10:37.070
But nobody talks. They all plead the fifth.

189
00:10:37.094 --> 00:10:39.281
With scant evidence and no body.

190
00:10:39.305 --> 00:10:41.700
the case of the missing
union leader goes colder

191
00:10:41.724 --> 00:10:43.893
than the Detroit river in February.

192
00:10:45.144 --> 00:10:49.541
In 1982. authorities declare
Jimmy hoffa legally dead.

193
00:10:49.565 --> 00:10:52.961
despite never in any way
answering what happened to him.

194
00:10:52.985 --> 00:10:56.548
The world is left mystified
as to his final fate.

195
00:10:56.572 --> 00:11:00.552
But then. 19 years later. a
game-changing revelation will

196
00:11:00.576 --> 00:11:02.328
crack the case wide open.

197
00:11:10.294 --> 00:11:14.316
In 2001. 19 years after
Jimmy hoffa went missing.

198
00:11:14.340 --> 00:11:17.176
a shocking discovery
jolts the case back into

199
00:11:17.301 --> 00:11:18.737
the national spotlight.

200
00:11:18.761 --> 00:11:23.158
DNA testing confirms the
hair found in the car is hoffa's.

201
00:11:23.182 --> 00:11:24.850
There's no longer any doubt.

202
00:11:24.975 --> 00:11:28.622
The infamous union boss
was inside that vehicle.

203
00:11:28.646 --> 00:11:31.833
But where was he taken?
And what was done to him?

204
00:11:31.857 --> 00:11:34.503
For over two decades. mafia historian.

205
00:11:34.527 --> 00:11:38.340
Christian cipollini. has dug
into the blood-soaked theories

206
00:11:38.364 --> 00:11:41.283
surrounding what happened
to hoffa and his body.

207
00:11:43.703 --> 00:11:47.599
The hoffa case fascinates me
because this is something that

208
00:11:47.623 --> 00:11:49.434
doesn't have closure.

209
00:11:49.458 --> 00:11:51.436
It's like the jfk assassination.

210
00:11:51.460 --> 00:11:54.046
It's like the disappearance
of Amelia earhart.

211
00:11:54.171 --> 00:11:55.339
We want some answers.

212
00:11:56.382 --> 00:12:00.821
One of the first major
theories that really stuck in

213
00:12:00.845 --> 00:12:04.950
the American psyche came
to light when a former mobster

214
00:12:04.974 --> 00:12:08.161
named Tony the Greek.
he said. hoffa was killed

215
00:12:08.185 --> 00:12:11.230
and then transported to New Jersey.

216
00:12:11.355 --> 00:12:15.043
and buried under the giants stadium.

217
00:12:15.067 --> 00:12:17.111
which they were building at the time.

218
00:12:17.236 --> 00:12:20.465
The problem with that
theory is that the mafia

219
00:12:20.489 --> 00:12:24.243
likes to do things in a practical way.

220
00:12:24.368 --> 00:12:25.745
Keep it simple.

221
00:12:25.870 --> 00:12:31.351
What the mob probably didn't
do was pack the body of the most

222
00:12:31.375 --> 00:12:35.814
famous missing man in america
on a truck. taking it across

223
00:12:35.838 --> 00:12:40.217
state lines to Bury it in
such an extravagant way.

224
00:12:42.553 --> 00:12:45.598
Rumors swelled into an urban
legend that Jimmy hoffa was

225
00:12:45.723 --> 00:12:47.826
buried in the stadium's foundations.

226
00:12:47.850 --> 00:12:49.935
But when it was demolished in 2010.

227
00:12:50.060 --> 00:12:51.771
no trace of him was found.

228
00:12:55.733 --> 00:12:59.653
Which leads us to popular
theory number two. the irishman.

229
00:12:59.779 --> 00:13:03.115
In 2003. frank sheer an.
a former teamster official

230
00:13:03.240 --> 00:13:06.553
and alleged mob
hitman. is dying of cancer.

231
00:13:06.577 --> 00:13:08.722
On his deathbed. he
gives a jaw-dropping

232
00:13:08.746 --> 00:13:10.039
confession to his lawyer.

233
00:13:11.457 --> 00:13:14.376
He claims hoffa was abducted
and murdered by the mob.

234
00:13:15.753 --> 00:13:18.356
Sheeran says he was not
only there that day. but he was

235
00:13:18.380 --> 00:13:20.341
the one who actually pulled the trigger.

236
00:13:22.134 --> 00:13:24.696
Sheeran's confession
becomes a best-selling book.

237
00:13:24.720 --> 00:13:26.847
later adapted into
Martin scorsese's movie.

238
00:13:26.972 --> 00:13:29.850
"the irishman." in which
he's played by Robert De Niro.

239
00:13:31.227 --> 00:13:34.247
Sheeran gives the exact
address of a house in Detroit where

240
00:13:34.271 --> 00:13:35.815
he claims hoffa was murdered.

241
00:13:44.490 --> 00:13:47.660
In 2004. investigators
tear up the floorboards

242
00:13:47.785 --> 00:13:49.596
and they do discover blood.

243
00:13:49.620 --> 00:13:52.081
Unfortunately. it's not a match for hoffa.

244
00:13:53.833 --> 00:13:57.312
The only evidence of frank
sheer an being involved in

245
00:13:57.336 --> 00:14:01.173
the hoffa hit and disappearance
